sentences.en: an insubstantial construction of wood and glue
sentences.cn: 用木头和胶粘合的简单构造

sentences.en: Early aircraft were insubstantial constructions of wood and glue.
sentences.cn: 早期的飞行器是木头和胶粘合的脆弱机器.

sentences.en: Finite personalities are insubstantial fragments of this engulfing spiritual unity.
sentences.cn: 有限的人格是这种兼容并包的精神统一的非实体的碎片.

sentences.en: Her limbs were insubstantial, almost transparent.
sentences.cn: 她的四肢非常纤细，几乎是透明的。

sentences.en: His world is, on the whole , made wonderfully interesting. But it is insubstantial.
sentences.cn: 他的世界大体说来写得非常有趣. 但是虚构的.

sentences.en: Mars has an insubstantial atmosphere, consisting almost entirely of carbon dioxide.
sentences.cn: 火星的大气层极其稀薄，几乎全部由二氧化碳构成。

sentences.en: the insubstantial outline of a ship
The rest were an insubstantial pageant.
sentences.cn: 其余的人都不过是华而不实的过眼烟云罢了.

sentences.en: Together, these particles form that most diffuse and insubstantial of substances -- interstellar dust.
sentences.cn: 聚集在一起, 这些微粒形成了大多数弥漫、脆弱的物质 —— 星际尘埃.

sentences.en: Void namely does not have the solid content, the insubstantial meaning.
sentences.cn: 空虚即无实在内容 、 不充实的意思.

sentences.en: Willy the Wizard is a very insubstantial booklet running to 36 pages which had limited distribution.
sentences.cn: 《魔法师威利》是一本仅有36页的小册子,内容十分空洞,发行量也很小.

words.tran_cn: 脆弱的；无实体的；幻想的，非真实的

trans.tran_cn: 无实体的，无实质的，非实在的
trans.tran_en: not solid, large, strong, or definite
